==技術細節==
The parameter name "dot-id" is used to define a braille cell. It is the numbering of the ''raised dots'', like {{code|1=136}} for {{braille cell|type=t|136}}. The sequence is climbing: 12345678, as is used in the Unicode character name: "Braille pattern dots-136".
*{{tl|Braille cell}}: separates numbered parameters into individual calls to /main.
*{{tl|Braille cell/main}}: calls /main2. Converts a single input code plus named parameters into appropriate braille cell id ("dot-id") and input code. Contains the list with non-English code translations (other languages).
*{{tl|Braille cell/main2}}: Calls /core. Prepares input texts and codes, using the now determined cell id. Checks for and shows error message.
*{{tl|Braille cell/core}}: Produces the actual cell output (text or image) using the settings.
* {{tl|braille cell/main2singlecell}}
* {{tl|braille cell/lang2lang-id}}

Input is evaluated and processed using these lists:
* {{tl|Braille cell/english&cell2dot-id}}: analyse input code against default list (English and generic)
* {{tl|Braille cell/dot-id2character}}: cell id into text character (Unicode)
* {{tl|Braille cell/dot-id2article}}: cell id into Wikipedia article name
* {{tl|Braille cell/dot-id2unicode-id}}: cell id into textual Unicode definition, pattern U+28xx
* {{tl|Braille cell/dot-id2filename}}: cell id into a specific filename (6dot, Japanese, Korean)
* {{tl|Braille cell/dot-id2filename-8dot}}: cell id into a default 8-dot filename

